<br>
Let it be known throughout the alliance that a challenge is hereby issued. On the 29th day of July of the year 2003 at 9:30PM EDT, teams from all across the realm are to gather for The First Annual Great Beer Swim Relay Races!<br>
<br>
The rules are as follows:<br>
<br>
* All participants are to join /beerswimrace for official news of the event. No drunken babble will be permitted.<br>
<br>
* A team shall be headed by a captain.<br>
<br>
* Each team will consist of four participants.<br>
<br>
* The captain shall designate the order each participant on his team will race, and communicate this to the Head Judge. <br>
<br>
* The teams will line up at the entrance to the Butcherblock docks.<br>
<br>
* The entrance will be the start and finish line.<br>
<br>
* At the start of the race, each participant in order as designated by the team captain, and proceeding one at a time, will then:<br>
--- chug five (5) short beers, <br>
--- run into the docks area, <br>
--- jump into the ocean,<br>
--- swim beyond the walls of the docks,<br>
--- head north in the water to the shore<br>
--- /poke the Midpoint Field Official<br>
--- run back to the starting line<br>
--- /poke the next person in order on their team<br>
--- in the case of the last person on each team, they must cross the finish line, i.e. the entrance to the docks area.<br>
<br>
* No speed enhancements of any kind shall be permitted!<br>
<br>
* Use of speed enhancements, failure to poke the Midpoint Field Judge, and failure to poke the next runner is grounds for disqualification and derrisive laughter.<br>
<br>
* No special consideration will be given to any team suffering a drowned participant.<br>
<br>
* The decision of the Judges is final.<br>
<br>
* The winning team will receive a prize purse of 400pp.<br>
<br>
* All other participating teams will receive a stack of these damn fishrolls and the great admiration of their peers.<br>
<br>
* All race beverages will be provided, and additional beverages will be provided for the festivities that are sure to follow.<br>
<br>
* Head Judge: Trevian<br>
* Midpoint Field Judge: Jatsya<br>
<br>
* May Tunare have mercy on you all.<br>
<br>
With that the bard nailed up the scroll to the board, bowed gracefully, and departed. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=169421" target="top">Trevian</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
